Followed along with a crash course that is located here
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Fdf5aTYRW0E

The follwing uses Angular 2.0 and Node.js to create a simple todolist that updates both locally and on the server. 
Uses a default todo list structure 

the code from the crash course can be found here
https://github.com/bradtraversy/angular-crash-todolist
